AD_TAB.NAME: Account
AD_TAB.HELP: The financial account window contains essential information such as the bank account number and allows to perform a set of processes such as to add deposit or withdrawal transactions to the financial account or to import and match a bank statement file.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Accounting information related to the material receipt
AD_TAB.HELP: Accounting information related to the material receipt
AD_TAB.HQLORDERBYCLAUSE: accountingSchema.name, accountingDate, abs(debit) desc, credit desc, value

AD_TAB.NAME: Prereserved Qty
AD_TAB.HELP: Relation of Reservations where the Purchase Order line has been used as prereservation.

AD_TAB.NAME: Lines
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Add products which are included in your goods receipt. Each product is shown on its own line.
AD_TAB.HELP: Once the goods receipt header has been properly filled in and saved each item received can be listed as a separate goods receipt line.

AD_TAB.NAME: Imported Bank Statements
AD_TAB.HELP: The tab lists the imported bank statement files as well as the bank statements created manually.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting History
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Accounting history
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab shows the accounting history of a given transaction.
AD_TAB.ORDERBYCLAUSE: DateAcct desc, Fin_FinAcc_Transaction_ID, Fact_Acct_Group_ID desc, seqno desc
AD_TAB.HQLORDERBYCLAUSE: accountingSchema.name, accountingDate, abs(debit) desc, credit desc, value

AD_TAB.NAME: Lines
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Add products and quantities for a specific goods movement. Each line represents one particular product.
AD_TAB.HELP: Lines tab is a list of the products moved between warehouses and storage bins.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting Configuration
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Relation of accounts used for the given financial account
AD_TAB.HELP: The accounting configuration tab is used to define the accounts of a General Ledger to use while posting transactions such as a bank fee or a deposit.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting
AD_TAB.HELP: The accounting tab is a read-only tab which showa every financial account transaction posting.
AD_TAB.ORDERBYCLAUSE: DateAcct desc, c_acctschema_id, Fact_Acct_Group_ID, docbasetype , Fin_FinAcc_Transaction_ID, seqno desc

AD_TAB.NAME: Transactions old 2
AD_TAB.HELP: The transaction tab lists all the deposit and withdrawal transactions of the financial account.

AD_TAB.NAME: Bank Statement Lines
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab list all the lines of a bank statement.

AD_TAB.NAME: Header
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Create and edit inventory internal movements.
AD_TAB.HELP: Internal inventory movements can be created by adding products to the lines tab or by moving all items at once.

AD_TAB.NAME: Header
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Create a requisition for procurement.
AD_TAB.HELP:
Procurement management team can perform several actions regarding requisitions.
This window allows them to manage requisitions regardless their current status, therefore they can change or close a requisition and create purchase orders for those demands.

AD_TAB.NAME: Lines
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Add products to be included in your requisition. Each product is added by creating a line.
AD_TAB.HELP: Procurement team can perform a set of actions regarding requisitions lines. It is possible for them to either create lines or product demands or to cancel them.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting dimension
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Accounting Dimension
AD_TAB.HELP: Accounting Dimension

AD_TAB.NAME: Transaction
AD_TAB.HQLFILTERCLAUSE: not exists (select 1 from FIN_Reconciliation r where r = e.reconciliation and r.processed = true)

AD_TAB.NAME: Header
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Create and edit a goods receipt.
AD_TAB.HELP: Goods Receipts can be issued and booked in the header section of the goods receipt window.
AD_TAB.HQLWHERECLAUSE: e.movementType IN ('V-', 'V+') and e.logistic = 'N' and e.documentType.return=false and e.organization.id = @#ad_org_id@

AD_TAB.NAME: Cleared items
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Cleared transactions
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab shows the transactions cleared or set as matched in a reconciliation.

AD_TAB.NAME: Payment Method
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Shows all payment methods related to the given financial account.
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab lists all the payment methods assigned to the financial account. A payment can either be deposited in or withdrawn from the financial account if the payment method used is assigned to the financial account.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting dimension
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Accounting Dimension
AD_TAB.HELP: Accounting Dimension

AD_TAB.NAME: Discounts and Promotions
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: View applied Discounts and Promotions for each line.
AD_TAB.HELP: View applied Discounts and Promotions for each line.

AD_TAB.NAME: Accounting
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Accounting information related to the goods movements
AD_TAB.HELP: Accounting information related to the goods movements
AD_TAB.HQLORDERBYCLAUSE: accountingSchema.name, accountingDate, abs(debit) desc, credit desc, value

AD_TAB.NAME: Line Tax
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Taxes related to the order line.
AD_TAB.HELP: For each purchase order line, Openbravo automatically populates the line tax related information in this tab.

AD_TAB.NAME: Exchange rates
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: In this tab the user can define another currency conversion rate for this document different than Openbravo systema exchange rate.
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab allows to define an exchange rate to use while posting the financial account transaction to the ledger whenever the currency of the financial account is not the same as the general ledger currency.

AD_TAB.NAME: Matched PO Lines
AD_TAB.HELP: This tab allows the procurement management team to either review the purchase order line automatically linked to a requisition line or to manually link an existing purchase order line to the corresponding requisition line.

AD_TAB.NAME: Reconciliations
AD_TAB.HELP: The reconciliation tab shows the reconciliations created manually if no matching algorithm is assigned to the financial account as well as the ones created while matching an imported bank statement file otherwise.

AD_TAB.NAME: Lines
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Add products to be included in your purchase order. Each product is added by creating a line.
AD_TAB.HELP: Once the purchase order header has been properly filled in and saved, each purchase order line can be created in this tab.

AD_TAB.NAME: Landed Cost
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Landed Cost tab allows to allocate additional costs to the goods receipt.
AD_TAB.HELP: Landed Cost tab allows to allocate additional costs to the goods receipt.

AD_TAB.NAME: Payment
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Create an obligation for accounting to pay for all or part of your purchase order amount in advance.
AD_TAB.HELP: Create an obligation for accounting to pay for all or part of your purchase order amount in advance.

AD_TAB.NAME: Payment Plan
AD_TAB.HELP: Shows the total amount expected to be paid upon order booking as well as the amount/s pre-paid or paid against the invoice/s for the order.

AD_TAB.NAME: Payment Details
AD_TAB.HELP: Displays the details of the payments (pre-payments or regular payments) made for the order or for the invoice/s of the order.

AD_TAB.NAME: Header
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Create a purchase order and process it when ready.
AD_TAB.HELP: Purchase orders can be created and booked in the header section of the purchase order window.

AD_TAB.NAME: Tax
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Edit taxes applied to your order.
AD_TAB.HELP: Summarized purchase order tax related information is shown in this tab.

AD_TAB.NAME: Basic Discounts
AD_TAB.HELP: Lists information about discounts automatically applied based on the supplier configuration and / or manually entered for the purchase order.
